WEBVTT

00:00:07.563 --> 00:00:11.021
Why did you decide to practice law,
Attorney Kujo?

00:00:13.396 --> 00:00:15.813
Are you interviewing me again?

00:00:20.396 --> 00:00:23.063
Then let me ask you in return.

00:00:24.188 --> 00:00:27.105
Why did you decide to practice law,
Attorney Karasuma?

00:00:29.605 --> 00:00:33.438
It goes back to when I attended
the trial for a certain case.

00:00:33.521 --> 00:00:38.105
When you killed your neighbor,
Toshiko Nakabayashi, with an axe,

00:00:38.188 --> 00:00:40.146
you were shrieking wildly, weren't you?

00:00:40.771 --> 00:00:44.188
The person living next door testified
that they heard you.

00:00:46.146 --> 00:00:49.146
"The content of my emails
is all over the internet."

00:00:49.230 --> 00:00:51.896
"You did this, you gossipy old hag."

00:00:52.771 --> 00:00:54.813
That's what you screamed, right?

00:00:55.730 --> 00:00:59.230
Why did you kill Toshiko Nakabayashi?

00:00:59.313 --> 00:01:00.771
Is this the reason?

00:01:01.271 --> 00:01:02.355
Why?

00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:05.105
She masterminded a secret society.

00:01:06.396 --> 00:01:09.646
She was monitoring my room every day
with that triangle eye.

00:01:10.938 --> 00:01:12.896
I realized the world's rulers planned

00:01:12.980 --> 00:01:15.438
to destroy humanity
with electromagnetic waves.

00:01:15.521 --> 00:01:17.021
In order to save the world,

00:01:17.105 --> 00:01:19.771
I exposed the mastermind's evil deeds
on the internet.

00:01:19.855 --> 00:01:23.730
The mastermind retaliated by attacking me
with an electromagnetic weapon,

00:01:23.813 --> 00:01:26.730
so I killed her in self-defense.

00:01:27.313 --> 00:01:28.730
Do you get it?

00:01:29.396 --> 00:01:33.688
You said you were taking
your medication every day.

00:01:35.230 --> 00:01:39.855
And you said the medication
left you disoriented. Is that correct?

00:01:40.605 --> 00:01:44.313
But you stopped going to the hospital
a month before the incident. Correct?

00:01:45.021 --> 00:01:48.438
You weren't on your meds
at the time of the crime, were you?

00:01:48.521 --> 00:01:51.563
-Defendant, return to your seat.
-What's that? Hey!

00:01:51.646 --> 00:01:53.188
What did you say?

00:01:55.105 --> 00:01:56.813
Allow me to change the subject.

00:01:57.688 --> 00:01:59.188
At the time of the crime,

00:01:59.688 --> 00:02:02.813
why did you steal
the victim's Shinkansen ticket

00:02:02.896 --> 00:02:03.980
and board the train?

00:02:04.063 --> 00:02:06.146
I received a divine message.

00:02:06.646 --> 00:02:10.855
I heard a voice telling me that the person
who'd sit next to me in the reserved seat

00:02:10.938 --> 00:02:13.021
would be the god who rules over darkness.

00:02:14.563 --> 00:02:16.563
On the Shinkansen,

00:02:16.646 --> 00:02:22.646
why did you kill Katsunobu Karasuma
with an ax when he tried to stop you?

00:02:24.105 --> 00:02:25.396
I…

00:02:26.021 --> 00:02:27.855
I'm the savior.

00:02:32.063 --> 00:02:34.980
-I am… the savior!
-Return to your seat!

00:02:35.063 --> 00:02:37.563
I am the savior!

00:02:37.646 --> 00:02:40.230
I am the savior!

00:02:42.063 --> 00:02:45.688
The circumstances of this case
are extremely heinous,

00:02:45.771 --> 00:02:49.563
and the defendant bears
grave criminal responsibility.

00:02:50.063 --> 00:02:54.855
In light of the crime's severity
and the need for general deterrence,

00:02:54.938 --> 00:02:57.396
the court finds it necessary

00:02:57.480 --> 00:03:02.438
to impose the death penalty.

00:03:04.021 --> 00:03:07.396
Those are the reasons for this judgment.

00:03:11.813 --> 00:03:13.438
That trial…

00:03:16.355 --> 00:03:18.480
I attended it too.

00:03:19.230 --> 00:03:20.313
I know.

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:22.855
That's why I came here.

00:03:23.563 --> 00:03:27.521
Attorney Sayama, thank you for your help.

00:03:27.605 --> 00:03:28.605
No…

00:03:29.271 --> 00:03:33.146
I'm relieved that we were able to achieve
a favorable result for your husband.

00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:34.313
Yes.

00:03:34.396 --> 00:03:39.438
I think Prosecutor Kurama's questioning
of the defendant was the deciding factor.

00:03:41.063 --> 00:03:42.480
Shinji,

00:03:42.980 --> 00:03:47.730
I'm going to go greet the defense team
and supporters with Attorney Sayama,

00:03:48.563 --> 00:03:50.271
so wait here for a bit.

00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:51.271
Okay.

00:03:52.521 --> 00:03:53.355
Okay. Let's go.

00:03:53.438 --> 00:03:54.438
Yes.

00:03:57.980 --> 00:04:00.813
This is wrong.
He shouldn't be getting the death penalty.

00:04:00.896 --> 00:04:04.021
That damn old man was smug.
He was pretending to be righteous.

00:04:04.105 --> 00:04:05.355
Hey,

00:04:05.438 --> 00:04:07.146
I won't allow you to badmouth Dad.

00:04:07.980 --> 00:04:11.771
Do you think nothing
of the questioning of the defendant?

00:04:11.855 --> 00:04:15.396
If that isn't considered insanity
under Article 39 of the Penal Code,

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:17.313
then what is?

00:04:17.396 --> 00:04:19.146
He should've been found not guilty.

00:04:19.230 --> 00:04:22.063
You're like a 2channeler
who's read a bit of the Six Codes.

00:04:22.146 --> 00:04:25.896
The media played up the victims'
families' grief to sway public opinion,

00:04:25.980 --> 00:04:27.813
and the court went along with it.

00:04:27.896 --> 00:04:30.896
It was a people's court
that prioritized emotions over facts.

00:04:31.396 --> 00:04:34.396
As long as humans keep creating trials,

00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:36.313
the law won't be the only influence.

00:04:36.938 --> 00:04:40.480
That's why we need to separate
mass psychology from the law.

00:04:40.563 --> 00:04:42.355
Stop whining, Taiza.

00:04:43.271 --> 00:04:45.521
Say that after you pass the bar exam.

00:04:49.105 --> 00:04:51.313
He was sentenced to death
in the first trial,

00:04:51.396 --> 00:04:54.563
but Attorney Nagaragi will get
life imprisonment in the appeal.

00:05:09.105 --> 00:05:11.480
I'll stick with you a little longer.

00:05:15.605 --> 00:05:16.855
Fine by me.

00:06:01.521 --> 00:06:02.938
All right. Here ya go!

00:06:04.438 --> 00:06:06.188
Tonight's a party, party.

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:14.605
Here.

00:06:15.188 --> 00:06:16.271
Thanks.

00:06:19.521 --> 00:06:21.063
Excuse me.

00:06:22.313 --> 00:06:24.063
Do you have a moment?

00:06:24.146 --> 00:06:25.188
Huh?

00:06:25.271 --> 00:06:27.146
What's in the bag?

00:06:28.646 --> 00:06:30.813
Uh, well, they're snacks.

00:06:30.896 --> 00:06:32.896
Do you mind if we check?

00:06:32.980 --> 00:06:34.438
Well, these are just snacks.

00:06:34.521 --> 00:06:37.355
-We'll confirm that.
-Oh, I'm sorry. Don't get mad at me.

00:06:37.438 --> 00:06:38.688
I'm not mad.

00:06:38.771 --> 00:06:41.605
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry…

00:06:41.688 --> 00:06:43.980
May I have a moment?

00:06:44.855 --> 00:06:47.146
Hey, what are you filming?

00:06:47.230 --> 00:06:48.980
You're interfering with our duties.

00:06:50.271 --> 00:06:55.688
Filming for a legitimate reason
isn't considered interference with duties.

00:06:55.771 --> 00:06:59.355
This is for preserving evidence
in case of an unlawful investigation.

00:06:59.438 --> 00:07:01.188
Who the hell are you?

00:07:03.646 --> 00:07:05.563
I'm an attorney

00:07:06.063 --> 00:07:07.313
with a nasty personality.

00:07:07.396 --> 00:07:08.771
An attorney?

00:07:10.313 --> 00:07:15.396
You all know that he's not obligated
to comply with a stop-and-frisk, right?

00:07:16.313 --> 00:07:18.896
Detaining someone
for a long time against their will

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:22.105
is considered an unlawful arrest
without a warrant.

00:07:22.188 --> 00:07:23.688
That's a violation of the law.

00:07:25.063 --> 00:07:28.563
If you're going to continue,
why don't you bring the papers?

00:07:30.271 --> 00:07:31.605
Excuse us.

00:07:38.021 --> 00:07:40.771
KUJO LAW OFFICE

00:07:47.646 --> 00:07:49.396
Do you not like spicy food?

00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:54.605
Oh, no… Is it okay
to make noise while eating?

00:07:55.105 --> 00:07:56.188
Of course.

00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:03.521
Mr. Sogabe, would you like water or tea?

00:08:03.605 --> 00:08:06.730
Oh, I'm fine with tap water.

00:08:13.271 --> 00:08:15.313
Sorry for the trouble. Thank you.

00:08:15.396 --> 00:08:18.230
You were in prison for a long time,
weren't you?

00:08:19.063 --> 00:08:19.938
Huh?

00:08:21.313 --> 00:08:23.146
Did you recently re-enter society?

00:08:24.355 --> 00:08:25.980
Why, w-why'd ya ask?

00:08:26.646 --> 00:08:30.855
You can't slurp. You can't choose
what you want to drink.

00:08:30.938 --> 00:08:35.563
That's all typical behavior of someone
who's been immersed in prison life.

00:08:38.230 --> 00:08:40.271
N-Nah! Nothing like that.

00:08:40.355 --> 00:08:42.688
Ugh, I'm sorry.

00:08:44.688 --> 00:08:45.730
Oh, sorry.

00:08:45.813 --> 00:08:46.855
Don't be.

00:08:46.938 --> 00:08:47.771
Here.

00:08:48.771 --> 00:08:49.813
POOP
STINKY

00:08:49.896 --> 00:08:51.813
That's an unusual tattoo.

00:08:51.896 --> 00:08:52.896
Huh?

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:53.855
Oh.

00:08:59.021 --> 00:09:00.021
Oh, hello?

00:09:00.521 --> 00:09:02.313
Two.

00:09:03.021 --> 00:09:04.813
The first ring, dimwit!

00:09:04.896 --> 00:09:06.063
Oh, sorry.

00:09:06.146 --> 00:09:07.771
The customer is waiting.

00:09:07.855 --> 00:09:10.646
Go real quick and get
those veggies delivered, okay?

00:09:10.730 --> 00:09:11.563
Okay.

00:09:11.646 --> 00:09:14.938
The police questioned you
because you were so out of it!

00:09:15.438 --> 00:09:18.355
You're paying for the lawyer.

00:09:18.438 --> 00:09:20.063
Sogabe,

00:09:20.146 --> 00:09:23.688
you're getting the tattoo
of shame punishment!

00:09:24.271 --> 00:09:25.646
What?!

00:09:28.146 --> 00:09:29.688
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:09:30.813 --> 00:09:33.521
Oh, thanks for the meal.

00:09:38.271 --> 00:09:40.438
Oh, I'm sorry. Excuse me.

00:09:50.438 --> 00:09:54.480
Attorney Kujo,
was that Sota Sogabe who just ran out?

00:09:54.563 --> 00:09:55.730
Yes.

00:09:55.813 --> 00:10:00.938
-Do you know him, Attorney Karasuma?
-Yes. I defended him six years ago.

00:10:07.938 --> 00:10:09.563
He forgot this.

00:10:16.146 --> 00:10:17.230
It's weed.

00:10:17.313 --> 00:10:18.480
What?

00:10:25.563 --> 00:10:26.980
What was his crime?

00:10:28.563 --> 00:10:33.438
He was sentenced to six years in prison
for robbery, causing injury.

00:10:36.938 --> 00:10:39.230
At the time, 21-year-old Sota Sogabe

00:10:39.313 --> 00:10:44.146
used 16-year-old boys
to commit the crime multiple times.

00:10:44.230 --> 00:10:45.438
However,

00:10:45.521 --> 00:10:48.355
Sogabe wasn't the real mastermind.

00:10:56.063 --> 00:10:56.980
Sorry.

00:10:59.688 --> 00:11:02.396
Sogabe, where are the veggies?

00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:03.313
Huh?

00:11:05.355 --> 00:11:08.021
-I forgot them at the lawyer's office.
-What?

00:11:08.896 --> 00:11:09.938
Here.

00:11:10.438 --> 00:11:11.271
Hey.

00:11:11.355 --> 00:11:12.605
Sorry, sorry.

00:11:12.688 --> 00:11:16.938
You're getting the tattoo
of shame punishment. Got it?

00:11:17.021 --> 00:11:19.063
The mastermind was Suguru Kanemoto.

00:11:19.146 --> 00:11:20.730
He's the son of a former yakuza

00:11:20.813 --> 00:11:22.938
and was once an aspiring sumo wrestler.

00:11:23.438 --> 00:11:26.063
Kanemoto and his friends
committed robbery and injury

00:11:26.146 --> 00:11:28.605
and put all the blame on Sogabe.

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.563
I see.

00:11:32.021 --> 00:11:33.813
Why was he here?

00:11:33.896 --> 00:11:37.771
It seems that Kanemoto guy
is Mibu's junior.

00:11:38.271 --> 00:11:40.896
I got a request
to help him escape from the police.

00:11:44.021 --> 00:11:48.688
It seems that Suguru Kanemoto
is making Sogabe do the job of a courier,

00:11:48.771 --> 00:11:51.271
which gives him the highest risk
of getting caught.

00:11:52.396 --> 00:11:56.480
He finally got out of prison,
but he's being used by Kanemoto again?

00:11:57.063 --> 00:12:00.063
How can we save Sogabe?

00:12:01.605 --> 00:12:03.105
How presumptuous of you.

00:12:03.188 --> 00:12:04.105
Huh?

00:12:05.938 --> 00:12:07.855
Attorneys can't save people.

00:12:09.271 --> 00:12:10.271
What do you mean?

00:12:13.605 --> 00:12:15.480
Would you like some coffee?

00:12:18.605 --> 00:12:20.855
How do Sogabe and Kanemoto
know each other?

00:12:22.313 --> 00:12:23.563
Through their fathers.

00:12:24.063 --> 00:12:29.313
Originally, Kanemoto's father violently
forced Sogabe's father to obey him.

00:12:30.188 --> 00:12:32.730
Suguru, can you use a guy like this?

00:12:32.813 --> 00:12:36.271
A great leader can make use
of useless subordinates.

00:12:36.355 --> 00:12:37.605
A great leader?

00:12:37.688 --> 00:12:42.146
Right now, I'm having him
deliver drugs for the same pay

00:12:42.230 --> 00:12:43.938
as a pizza delivery guy.

00:12:44.021 --> 00:12:45.188
Are you serious?

00:12:45.271 --> 00:12:47.396
Can't believe he's risking getting busted.

00:12:47.980 --> 00:12:51.146
Our families live close to each other.

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:55.063
His father used to get shaken down
by my father all the time.

00:12:55.771 --> 00:13:00.938
He'd take his money playing Oicho-Kabu,
even though he didn't even know the rules.

00:13:02.813 --> 00:13:03.688
Hey.

00:13:04.855 --> 00:13:08.396
Hey, Sogabe,
if you can't follow my orders,

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:11.605
I'll tattoo you in the same spot
as your father.

00:13:11.688 --> 00:13:13.188
Stop, stop.

00:13:13.271 --> 00:13:14.771
What do you mean by that?

00:13:14.855 --> 00:13:17.938
Oh, when my old man was in a bad mood,

00:13:18.021 --> 00:13:21.813
he used to tattoo his father
on the forehead with a toothpick.

00:13:21.896 --> 00:13:22.896
He wrote "poop."

00:13:24.188 --> 00:13:26.355
Is your father a tattoo artist?

00:13:26.438 --> 00:13:28.730
He's just a yakuza.

00:13:28.813 --> 00:13:33.605
Then this guy tried to protect his father
and resisted, saying, "Stop it."

00:13:34.188 --> 00:13:36.771
For someone named Sogabe,
you're full of yourself!

00:13:36.855 --> 00:13:38.771
Well, you sure did get on my nerves!

00:13:40.105 --> 00:13:41.396
So,

00:13:41.480 --> 00:13:42.605
I asked my father

00:13:43.355 --> 00:13:45.313
to tattoo this guy's arm too.

00:13:45.396 --> 00:13:46.230
POOP

00:13:46.313 --> 00:13:50.230
So, that tattoo was done
by Kanemoto's father?

00:13:50.313 --> 00:13:51.605
Yeah.

00:13:52.146 --> 00:13:54.980
I hear that amateur tattoos,
due to their varying depths,

00:13:55.063 --> 00:13:56.896
are hard to remove, even by doctors.

00:14:00.146 --> 00:14:04.063
For the rest of your lives,
you and your father are gonna have to live

00:14:04.146 --> 00:14:06.188
with being branded "poop."

00:14:07.063 --> 00:14:08.563
Whoa. You're messed up.

00:14:10.230 --> 00:14:11.105
Boom!

00:14:14.146 --> 00:14:15.688
Don't you criticize me.

00:14:17.271 --> 00:14:18.438
I…

00:14:18.521 --> 00:14:19.480
I'm sorry.

00:14:21.813 --> 00:14:25.938
Sogabe went to prison
in place of Kanemoto and his friends,

00:14:26.021 --> 00:14:28.021
and it seems like he went through a lot.

00:14:29.605 --> 00:14:32.063
They made him eat vomit.

00:14:32.605 --> 00:14:35.230
They stabbed him with pencils
where it wouldn't show.

00:14:36.230 --> 00:14:38.271
They made him carry out sexual favors.

00:14:39.396 --> 00:14:41.771
Every day must have been hell.

00:14:44.063 --> 00:14:46.605
Why did he get close to Kanemoto again?

00:14:49.063 --> 00:14:53.563
It's not easy to escape a vicious cycle.

00:14:54.896 --> 00:14:56.313
Vicious cycle?

00:14:59.521 --> 00:15:01.521
Anyway, this room…

00:15:02.688 --> 00:15:04.521
It stinks.

00:15:04.605 --> 00:15:07.813
Apparently, someone died alone
or committed suicide here.

00:15:07.896 --> 00:15:10.980
The body was left to rot.
This room is a stigmatized property.

00:15:11.063 --> 00:15:11.980
Oh.

00:15:14.605 --> 00:15:15.730
I see.

00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:19.688
I hear the smell of a dead body
is hard to get rid of.

00:15:22.313 --> 00:15:24.896
Mmm, not bad.

00:15:24.980 --> 00:15:25.980
With this smell?

00:15:26.063 --> 00:15:27.021
Hey.

00:15:30.605 --> 00:15:31.980
Sogabe,

00:15:32.646 --> 00:15:35.271
I'm sorry for saying terrible things.

00:15:35.355 --> 00:15:37.355
Nah. Um…

00:15:38.313 --> 00:15:41.313
I've never been good
at keeping my cool, and I just lost it…

00:15:41.396 --> 00:15:43.938
No, no. I understand.

00:15:44.938 --> 00:15:46.688
I'm the one who screwed up.

00:15:46.771 --> 00:15:50.313
No, no. You've always saved us, Sogabe.

00:15:50.396 --> 00:15:51.730
No, no.

00:15:51.813 --> 00:15:55.355
Seeing you as a real man I can count on,
I have a favor to ask.

00:15:55.438 --> 00:15:56.771
A favor?

00:15:56.855 --> 00:16:00.646
We'd like to rent your place
to use as a room

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:03.063
to divide marijuana
and cocaine into portions.

00:16:05.813 --> 00:16:06.855
Cocaine?

00:16:06.938 --> 00:16:10.688
We've been in a bind since the higher-ups
ordered us to handle cocaine.

00:16:12.230 --> 00:16:13.771
Please help us.

00:16:26.980 --> 00:16:28.938
Excuse me.

00:16:29.730 --> 00:16:30.646
Huh?

00:16:31.230 --> 00:16:32.063
Huh?

00:16:33.480 --> 00:16:35.730
What's wrong, Mr. Sogabe?

00:16:35.813 --> 00:16:38.688
I came to pick up something I left behind.

00:16:39.188 --> 00:16:40.105
Huh?

00:16:40.771 --> 00:16:42.105
This, right?

00:16:43.396 --> 00:16:45.688
Oh, that's it.

00:16:46.521 --> 00:16:47.980
Thanks so much--

00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:51.021
Do you know what's inside?

00:16:53.188 --> 00:16:54.563
They're snacks.

00:16:55.855 --> 00:16:57.813
Hello, Mr. Sogabe. It's been a while.

00:16:57.896 --> 00:16:59.188
Oh…

00:16:59.271 --> 00:17:03.146
-I'm Attorney Karasuma. Ring any bells?
-Oh, Attorney Karasuma.

00:17:03.230 --> 00:17:05.980
Thank you for that time. Thank you.

00:17:06.063 --> 00:17:09.271
If you have any trouble again,
please contact me anytime.

00:17:09.355 --> 00:17:10.271
Oh…

00:17:11.063 --> 00:17:12.605
Yeah.

00:17:14.188 --> 00:17:19.230
-Mr. Sogabe?
-There's nothing I can ask a lawyer to do.

00:17:19.313 --> 00:17:21.230
Besides, I don't have any money.

00:17:21.313 --> 00:17:25.230
And I have no clue about the law,
so I have nothing to do with you. Yup.

00:17:25.313 --> 00:17:26.271
Thanks.

00:17:26.355 --> 00:17:29.230
But aren't you being used
by Mr. Kanemoto again?

00:17:29.980 --> 00:17:31.355
I'm not being used!

00:17:34.188 --> 00:17:36.271
Don't look down on me 'cause I'm stupid.

00:17:37.396 --> 00:17:39.521
Shouldn't a senior protect his juniors?

00:17:39.605 --> 00:17:41.313
-Mr. Sogabe.
-What?

00:17:42.605 --> 00:17:44.521
I'm not looking down on you.

00:17:45.646 --> 00:17:46.646
Oh…

00:17:49.688 --> 00:17:51.646
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:54.355
It's just, I've always been
the one everyone's teased

00:17:54.438 --> 00:17:57.438
since I was a kid,
'cause I'm slow, so, like…

00:17:57.521 --> 00:17:59.063
It's no wonder you think that.

00:17:59.146 --> 00:18:00.146
Mr. Sogabe.

00:18:00.230 --> 00:18:01.730
Yes. Yes?

00:18:02.271 --> 00:18:05.480
An attorney's job is to listen to people.

00:18:05.563 --> 00:18:08.813
The first consultation is free,
so it doesn't cost money.

00:18:08.896 --> 00:18:10.563
Feel free to come anytime.

00:18:15.938 --> 00:18:17.271
Oh, thank you. Excuse me.

00:18:23.271 --> 00:18:24.730
Attorney Karasuma.

00:18:26.605 --> 00:18:30.230
Do you know why Sogabe
hangs out with Kanemoto?

00:18:31.230 --> 00:18:33.230
Well, it's because he's scared.

00:18:33.313 --> 00:18:35.730
There's an advantage
to hanging out with him.

00:18:36.730 --> 00:18:39.396
An advantage that only exists
in Sogabe's world.

00:18:49.146 --> 00:18:50.146
Hey.

00:18:53.105 --> 00:18:55.063
What are you glaring at me for?

00:18:55.146 --> 00:18:57.146
Hand over your money, or I'll kill you.

00:18:59.063 --> 00:19:00.646
Who are you talkin' to?

00:19:01.230 --> 00:19:02.313
Huh?

00:19:03.021 --> 00:19:04.355
Who the hell are you guys?

00:19:04.438 --> 00:19:05.521
Huh?

00:19:05.605 --> 00:19:08.355
What's wrong, Sogabe?

00:19:10.396 --> 00:19:11.563
What?

00:19:12.438 --> 00:19:14.771
You got a problem with Sogabe?

00:19:14.855 --> 00:19:16.355
Oh, uh…

00:19:17.771 --> 00:19:19.646
-Here.
-Thank you for your hard work.

00:19:22.605 --> 00:19:24.771
We'll take care of the rest.

00:19:25.355 --> 00:19:26.271
Yeah.

00:19:29.646 --> 00:19:31.688
All right. This way, this way.

00:19:31.771 --> 00:19:32.605
Yes.

00:19:32.688 --> 00:19:34.063
Ow, that hurts…

00:19:34.146 --> 00:19:38.105
That's right. We found
a good room to divide it up.

00:19:38.605 --> 00:19:39.605
Yes.

00:19:40.188 --> 00:19:41.188
Yes.

00:19:41.730 --> 00:19:43.521
I appreciate your business.

00:19:47.730 --> 00:19:49.396
Prosperity!

00:19:49.938 --> 00:19:51.605
Prosperity!

00:19:52.146 --> 00:19:55.021
It's the mighty Suguru Kanemoto's story

00:19:56.188 --> 00:19:58.896
of prosperity!

00:19:58.980 --> 00:20:00.855
You're in a good mood, Suguru.

00:20:01.355 --> 00:20:03.063
Take that. And that!

00:20:04.938 --> 00:20:06.271
You guys

00:20:06.355 --> 00:20:08.646
not only messed with Sogabe,

00:20:08.730 --> 00:20:12.855
but you had the nerve
to do business on our turf.

00:20:14.813 --> 00:20:15.730
Huh?

00:20:18.355 --> 00:20:20.688
Huh? Aren't these guys dead?

00:20:20.771 --> 00:20:21.688
Hey.

00:20:21.771 --> 00:20:23.896
We meant to half-kill them,

00:20:23.980 --> 00:20:26.355
but I guess
we pretty much killed them for good.

00:20:27.188 --> 00:20:29.230
Well, even if they are dead,

00:20:29.313 --> 00:20:33.813
we have Sogabe, our guardian angel,
to take the fall for us.

00:20:34.605 --> 00:20:35.980
That's true!

00:20:37.188 --> 00:20:38.938
Everyone should have a Sogabe.

00:20:39.980 --> 00:20:41.563
Well said, well said!

00:20:41.646 --> 00:20:43.188
Suguru!

00:20:43.271 --> 00:20:44.188
Miyoko?

00:20:44.688 --> 00:20:45.563
Miyoko.

00:20:45.646 --> 00:20:47.313
Let's go home.

00:20:47.396 --> 00:20:51.438
We're having your favorite
sweet curry hot pot tonight.

00:20:51.521 --> 00:20:53.438
Yay!

00:20:54.563 --> 00:20:56.396
-Clean this up, will ya?
-Sure thing.

00:20:57.771 --> 00:20:59.105
You're late!

00:20:59.188 --> 00:21:05.271
Today, it's Miyoko, me, and curry.

00:21:11.605 --> 00:21:15.396
Just watching you eat makes me feel full.

00:21:17.105 --> 00:21:19.730
Then can I have
all of this pork and pepper stir-fry?

00:21:19.813 --> 00:21:21.438
Go right ahead.

00:21:23.230 --> 00:21:27.313
So you wanted to talk to me. Whatcha got?

00:21:27.396 --> 00:21:30.063
Do you remember Sota Sogabe?

00:21:30.146 --> 00:21:31.021
Of course.

00:21:31.105 --> 00:21:32.730
When he got out of prison,

00:21:32.813 --> 00:21:35.230
I helped him find a job
and a place to live

00:21:35.313 --> 00:21:37.396
as part of his post-release support.

00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:41.396
But in less than a month,
I lost contact with him.

00:21:42.105 --> 00:21:44.313
He hasn't been in touch with his parents.

00:21:44.396 --> 00:21:46.896
He's committed another crime.

00:21:47.771 --> 00:21:49.813
What? Really?

00:21:50.563 --> 00:21:52.646
Yes, I'm sure of it.

00:21:54.188 --> 00:21:57.480
Ugh, Sota Sogabe!

00:21:57.563 --> 00:22:00.438
That idiot! Why?

00:22:01.021 --> 00:22:05.396
So, I'd like to ask for your help
with his rehabilitation.

00:22:05.480 --> 00:22:06.938
What a damn idiot.

00:22:07.021 --> 00:22:09.938
Don't say that. Let's try again. Together.

00:22:10.021 --> 00:22:12.396
I'm sure that's what
Attorney Kujo wants too.

00:22:14.105 --> 00:22:15.521
Excuse me. Another beer.

00:22:17.230 --> 00:22:18.521
Here ya go.

00:22:18.605 --> 00:22:19.730
Thanks.

00:22:19.813 --> 00:22:21.230
Thanks.

00:22:21.313 --> 00:22:22.355
Well, see ya.

00:22:22.438 --> 00:22:23.313
Bye-bye.

00:22:23.396 --> 00:22:25.813
The marijuana customers look happy.

00:22:31.438 --> 00:22:33.730
It's good stuff. Give me three packets.

00:22:33.813 --> 00:22:34.855
Sure.

00:22:36.396 --> 00:22:37.271
Okay.

00:22:37.355 --> 00:22:38.521
Here ya go.

00:22:41.271 --> 00:22:45.271
-And this is my pee.
-A good luck charm for my urine test.

00:22:46.271 --> 00:22:47.355
You're welcome.

00:22:48.146 --> 00:22:49.146
Enjoy yourself.

00:22:49.771 --> 00:22:53.313
The cocaine customers
are rich party people.

00:22:54.146 --> 00:22:55.813
-You wanna fight?
-No, I don't.

00:22:55.896 --> 00:22:58.563
-Give me the meth!
-No, we don't sell meth.

00:22:58.646 --> 00:23:00.646
Just give it to me!

00:23:00.730 --> 00:23:02.896
I've got money!

00:23:04.396 --> 00:23:06.188
Excuse me.

00:23:06.271 --> 00:23:09.605
The stimulant drug customers
are mostly the old and the poor.

00:23:10.563 --> 00:23:12.271
Being at the bottom is a bummer.

00:23:15.938 --> 00:23:18.313
What I do now is bad,

00:23:18.396 --> 00:23:21.563
but since they want it and are happy,
it's not the worst thing.

00:23:22.105 --> 00:23:24.271
Eight years ago,
I attacked middle-aged men.

00:23:24.355 --> 00:23:26.730
I felt bad for the victims,
and it made me sick.

00:23:28.813 --> 00:23:30.688
You must be Sota Sogabe.

00:23:31.188 --> 00:23:32.688
Can we have a moment?

00:23:36.938 --> 00:23:38.355
-Hey, wait up! Hey!
-Sogabe!

00:23:38.438 --> 00:23:39.438
Ouch!

00:23:41.480 --> 00:23:42.355
I'm sorry.

00:23:42.438 --> 00:23:45.563
Wow, so cute!

00:23:45.646 --> 00:23:48.146
Come on, Rino. Say something to Daddy.

00:23:48.730 --> 00:23:51.105
Thank you for the present, Daddy.

00:23:51.188 --> 00:23:52.855
Good luck with your work.

00:23:53.438 --> 00:23:55.188
Good luck.

00:23:55.271 --> 00:23:56.438
KENGO MIBU

00:23:58.146 --> 00:23:59.146
See you--

00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:04.188
Hello. It's Kujo.

00:24:05.688 --> 00:24:08.355
Sota Sogabe has been arrested.

00:24:08.438 --> 00:24:09.438
On what charges?

00:24:10.813 --> 00:24:12.021
Possession of marijuana

00:24:13.271 --> 00:24:14.521
and cocaine.

00:24:16.355 --> 00:24:17.480
Cocaine?

00:24:19.230 --> 00:24:23.730
Three grams of cocaine and four grams of
dried marijuana were found at your home.

00:24:24.313 --> 00:24:27.063
You're lucky it was a small amount
after it was divided.

00:24:27.146 --> 00:24:29.855
But you have a prior criminal record,

00:24:29.938 --> 00:24:33.230
so you won't be able
to avoid a prison sentence.

00:24:34.230 --> 00:24:39.230
By the way, did you hear that Mr. Kanemoto
was arrested as an accomplice?

00:24:39.855 --> 00:24:41.271
Kanemoto was?

00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:44.105
No, I didn't know.

00:24:45.313 --> 00:24:46.730
Mr. Sogabe.

00:24:47.313 --> 00:24:50.438
Why don't you use
this opportunity to be honest?

00:24:51.730 --> 00:24:52.605
Honest?

00:24:52.688 --> 00:24:55.438
Tell them you committed the robbery
and had the drugs

00:24:55.521 --> 00:24:59.021
because Mr. Kanemoto threatened you.

00:25:01.146 --> 00:25:04.855
You know Ms. Yakushimae,
the criminal justice social worker, right?

00:25:06.563 --> 00:25:09.855
I asked her to prepare a shelter for you

00:25:09.938 --> 00:25:13.355
so that Mr. Kanemoto
won't attack you if you get bail.

00:25:14.438 --> 00:25:16.646
You can break the vicious cycle here.

00:25:17.980 --> 00:25:20.563
If it's to that end,
I'll do anything to help you.

00:25:20.646 --> 00:25:22.480
-That's no good.
-What?

00:25:26.938 --> 00:25:28.271
Mr. Sogabe,

00:25:29.271 --> 00:25:32.313
don't spill anything
about Suguru Kanemoto.

00:25:33.021 --> 00:25:34.563
Take the blame for everything.

00:25:34.646 --> 00:25:36.146
What are you saying?

00:25:36.230 --> 00:25:38.480
That kind of advice
will get you disbarred.

00:25:38.563 --> 00:25:41.021
No one will know
if the three of us keep quiet.

00:25:41.646 --> 00:25:42.813
Then I'm out.

00:25:44.105 --> 00:25:45.021
Go ahead.

00:25:51.980 --> 00:25:55.396
Are you going to make him do
the same thing again, Attorney Kujo?

00:25:56.480 --> 00:25:59.146
Why are you protecting
a bad guy like Kanemoto?

00:25:59.230 --> 00:26:02.688
That'll leave Mr. Sogabe stuck
in this situation for his entire life.

00:26:02.771 --> 00:26:04.646
It'll cause his parents great sorrow.

00:26:04.730 --> 00:26:05.605
That's fine.

00:26:06.605 --> 00:26:07.480
What?

00:26:09.980 --> 00:26:11.730
That's fine. That's okay.

00:26:13.646 --> 00:26:15.480
I'll take the blame for everything.

00:26:17.480 --> 00:26:18.646
Well…

00:26:20.396 --> 00:26:22.105
I remember

00:26:22.188 --> 00:26:24.896
this one field day when I was a kid.

00:26:26.230 --> 00:26:29.271
I was a klutz.

00:26:29.896 --> 00:26:32.230
I always came last in races.

00:26:32.313 --> 00:26:37.896
Everyone in the schoolyard
would cheer me on and clap.

00:26:38.563 --> 00:26:42.438
I desperately looked for my mom.

00:26:44.146 --> 00:26:45.271
And then…

00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:47.813
She was looking down,

00:26:47.896 --> 00:26:51.063
and she was looking like
it was the end of the world.

00:26:53.896 --> 00:26:56.730
I think she was embarrassed
and frustrated.

00:26:57.313 --> 00:26:58.313
Because of me.

00:27:00.646 --> 00:27:05.355
So if a piece of trash like me can be
of use to someone, I'll do anything.

00:27:06.063 --> 00:27:08.146
-Mr. Sogabe--
-Understood.

00:27:08.813 --> 00:27:12.021
Then we'll proceed in this direction.

00:27:14.438 --> 00:27:16.230
Are you sure about this?

00:27:25.646 --> 00:27:27.605
Kanemoto.

00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:30.146
Say something already.

00:27:34.521 --> 00:27:37.271
Don't think a half-assed punk like you…

00:27:38.438 --> 00:27:41.271
can get away with staying silent.

00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:48.521
Attorney Kujo,

00:27:48.605 --> 00:27:52.188
taking on Sogabe's
and Kanemoto's defense at the same time

00:27:52.271 --> 00:27:54.313
could be a conflict of interest.

00:27:54.813 --> 00:27:57.605
It's something that
an attorney shouldn't do.

00:27:58.105 --> 00:28:00.230
If they're both satisfied
with the results,

00:28:00.313 --> 00:28:02.480
they won't report me
to the bar association,

00:28:02.563 --> 00:28:04.021
and there won't be a hearing.

00:28:04.521 --> 00:28:05.938
There won't be any problems.

00:28:06.646 --> 00:28:08.938
Is that how you do things?

00:28:09.855 --> 00:28:11.063
Go in.

00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:21.896
You look worn out, Mr. Kanemoto.

00:28:23.271 --> 00:28:26.146
This is my first time being interrogated.

00:28:28.730 --> 00:28:29.813
But more importantly,

00:28:30.813 --> 00:28:32.605
did that bastard Sogabe fess up?

00:28:32.688 --> 00:28:33.688
No.

00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:35.896
I swear he hasn't done that.

00:28:41.021 --> 00:28:42.771
Listen, Mr. Kanemoto.

00:28:44.188 --> 00:28:47.730
The police will try to brainwash you
over the next 20 days.

00:28:48.730 --> 00:28:51.521
Lies will get called out,
so don't say anything.

00:28:52.021 --> 00:28:52.896
Keep silent.

00:28:53.938 --> 00:28:55.605
Yes, sir.

00:28:56.438 --> 00:28:58.688
Attorneys have unlimited visitation time.

00:28:59.355 --> 00:29:01.938
If it gets really tough,
I can visit you anytime.

00:29:03.896 --> 00:29:06.063
Remain silent for 20 days.

00:29:07.396 --> 00:29:11.396
You'll be out in 20 days without charges,
pending further investigation.

00:29:11.480 --> 00:29:13.063
You likely won't be prosecuted.

00:29:13.146 --> 00:29:14.105
Got it?

00:29:14.688 --> 00:29:16.271
Yes, sir.

00:29:16.855 --> 00:29:18.730
From talking to the detectives,

00:29:18.813 --> 00:29:23.230
they don't seem to have
any decisive evidence of your involvement.

00:29:23.313 --> 00:29:25.646
If the police try to threaten or coax you,

00:29:25.730 --> 00:29:28.896
that means they're getting flustered.

00:29:28.980 --> 00:29:30.938
If that happens, we win. Remember that.

00:29:31.021 --> 00:29:33.521
Yes, sir.

00:29:35.146 --> 00:29:38.813
I can't give you a spiral notebook
since the wire can be used as a weapon.

00:29:39.313 --> 00:29:41.855
I'll bring you a regular notebook later,

00:29:41.938 --> 00:29:44.230
so take notes
of the interrogation every day.

00:29:44.313 --> 00:29:45.146
Understood.

00:29:45.230 --> 00:29:47.730
Write one page every day.

00:29:47.813 --> 00:29:49.855
You'll be out in 20 days. Hang in there.

00:29:49.938 --> 00:29:51.855
Yes, sir.

00:29:51.938 --> 00:29:53.188
I'll do my best.

00:29:53.271 --> 00:29:56.688
You used violence
to make Mr. Sogabe obey you.

00:29:56.771 --> 00:30:00.021
But now that you've been caught,
you're very obedient.

00:30:00.105 --> 00:30:01.438
Huh?

00:30:01.521 --> 00:30:04.230
You only bare your fangs at the weak,

00:30:04.313 --> 00:30:06.896
and you bow before the strong,
such as attorneys.

00:30:07.896 --> 00:30:10.355
How cowardly and devious can you be?

00:30:10.438 --> 00:30:13.355
Hey, Attorney Kujo. What's with this guy?

00:30:14.896 --> 00:30:15.938
He's my colleague.

00:30:16.730 --> 00:30:19.813
I'm just helping Attorney Kujo
because it's my job.

00:30:20.313 --> 00:30:22.855
But I don't like people like you.

00:30:22.938 --> 00:30:26.521
Bring it on, dipshit!
Attorney Kujo, get him off this case!

00:30:26.605 --> 00:30:29.021
No, I won't get him off the case.

00:30:29.813 --> 00:30:31.771
What's your problem?

00:30:31.855 --> 00:30:33.730
-Sit down!
-Don't mess with me!

00:30:33.813 --> 00:30:35.480
Kanemoto, what are you doing?

00:30:35.563 --> 00:30:36.438
Damn you!

00:30:36.521 --> 00:30:38.480
Calm down. Cut it out!

00:30:38.563 --> 00:30:41.355
Don't mess with me.
You infuriating piece of shit!

00:30:41.438 --> 00:30:42.271
Don't resist!

00:30:42.355 --> 00:30:43.688
Don't mess with me. Hey!

00:30:44.771 --> 00:30:45.688
Miyoko!

00:30:48.938 --> 00:30:50.605
Hey, you crooked lawyer.

00:30:50.688 --> 00:30:51.521
Hi there.

00:30:51.605 --> 00:30:53.271
What the hell is your intention?

00:30:54.271 --> 00:30:56.688
You're putting all the blame on Sogabe.

00:30:56.771 --> 00:31:00.855
And you're letting Suguru Kanemoto
off the hook. How could you do that?

00:31:00.938 --> 00:31:02.396
What are you thinking?

00:31:03.063 --> 00:31:06.938
What do you mean, what? I'm trying
to get Sogabe a lighter sentence.

00:31:07.563 --> 00:31:08.813
What?

00:31:08.896 --> 00:31:12.438
He has a criminal record,
so he can't avoid a prison sentence.

00:31:13.063 --> 00:31:16.605
Since he'll be convicted again
within five years of leaving prison,

00:31:16.688 --> 00:31:18.146
his sentence will be heavier.

00:31:19.271 --> 00:31:21.313
Attorney Karasuma, is this true?

00:31:22.188 --> 00:31:23.438
Well, yes.

00:31:24.896 --> 00:31:27.771
So here's the issue in the trial…

00:31:28.271 --> 00:31:31.730
It's whether Sogabe possessed
the drugs for profit,

00:31:31.813 --> 00:31:36.730
or if it was simple possession
for personal use.

00:31:37.313 --> 00:31:39.230
What's the difference between the two?

00:31:39.938 --> 00:31:42.980
The police found a digital scale
and packets in his home.

00:31:43.063 --> 00:31:46.355
They got him for possession for profit.
He could get three years.

00:31:46.938 --> 00:31:48.605
But if it were simple possession,

00:31:48.688 --> 00:31:51.896
the prison sentence
would likely be around a year and a half.

00:31:51.980 --> 00:31:53.355
Exactly.

00:31:53.438 --> 00:31:57.313
If they reject his involvement with
Kanemoto, the crime looks less organized,

00:31:57.396 --> 00:32:00.688
and the case will lean
towards simple possession.

00:32:03.771 --> 00:32:05.480
So what's your complaint?

00:32:06.605 --> 00:32:09.980
I'm not here
because I wanted to talk about the law.

00:32:10.063 --> 00:32:12.896
I wanted to say
that this is ethically wrong.

00:32:14.230 --> 00:32:15.271
Ethically?

00:32:15.355 --> 00:32:17.688
Sogabe, who was completely clueless,

00:32:17.771 --> 00:32:20.355
was just following
Suguru Kanemoto's orders

00:32:20.438 --> 00:32:21.980
and was being used by him.

00:32:22.063 --> 00:32:24.271
The way he's being treated now is cruel.

00:32:25.563 --> 00:32:27.063
He knows.

00:32:27.563 --> 00:32:28.438
What?

00:32:28.521 --> 00:32:32.396
Sogabe understands reason and logic
better than you think.

00:32:32.980 --> 00:32:34.813
What? Reason and logic?

00:32:35.938 --> 00:32:37.896
Talking people into things

00:32:37.980 --> 00:32:41.813
and shifting the burden
onto those in a weaker position.

00:32:41.896 --> 00:32:44.021
Is that what you call reason and logic?

00:32:44.105 --> 00:32:46.230
That's wrong.

00:32:46.313 --> 00:32:49.396
Aren't attorney's supposed to
protect the weak?

00:32:51.188 --> 00:32:54.188
What you're doing
is ethically unacceptable.

00:32:54.271 --> 00:32:56.188
It's wrong, for sure.

00:33:07.813 --> 00:33:10.438
Do you think so, too, Attorney Karasuma?

00:33:11.313 --> 00:33:14.980
I can't say for sure that it's wrong.

00:33:15.063 --> 00:33:16.146
But…

00:33:16.813 --> 00:33:17.646
But?

00:33:17.730 --> 00:33:20.438
I'll save Sogabe in my own way.

00:33:36.105 --> 00:33:37.771
Hello, this is Kujo.

00:33:38.355 --> 00:33:40.605
How did it go?

00:33:41.271 --> 00:33:44.896
I've decided to have Mr. Sogabe
take the blame for everything.

00:33:45.813 --> 00:33:47.480
No fessing up about Mr. Kanemoto.

00:33:47.563 --> 00:33:52.396
In return, Mr. Kanemoto will stay silent
and get cut loose in 20 days.

00:33:53.855 --> 00:33:55.063
I see.

00:33:56.480 --> 00:34:00.646
If you can actually pull that off,
you're a genius.

00:34:55.938 --> 00:34:58.146
All right. Let's go eat.

00:35:11.771 --> 00:35:13.230
Excuse me.

00:35:14.021 --> 00:35:16.021
You're Sota Sogabe's father, right?

00:35:16.105 --> 00:35:16.938
POOP
STINKY

00:35:17.021 --> 00:35:18.355
Huh? Yes, uh…

00:35:18.938 --> 00:35:21.146
I'm Attorney Karasuma.

00:35:21.938 --> 00:35:25.521
I want to cut ties between
your son and Suguru Kanemoto.

00:35:26.896 --> 00:35:29.063
Would you be willing to cooperate?

00:38:14.230 --> 00:38:17.605
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa